values:
Well, Khan, my cat, seems to keep cutting his right back leg on god knows what. There's literally nothing on the floor or anywhere he gets onto that he can cut himself on. I've taken him to the vet twice because of a past abscess and his thyroid, and his monthly thyroid medication, and Akasha just went last week, so I'm tapped out on money.

His back leg has started to swell, so I  know there's probably a bacterial infection or an abscess. I cleaned it out with warm, soapy water, rubbing alcohol, and covered it in honey, and I made him lick some off my finger as a sort of antibacterial/antibiotic kind of thing. I'm really hoping this works. If anyone else has some home remedies they'd like to share, please go ahead and do so!
Hey gais. Gais. I just had my first photo-reblog on tumblr. 8D Is it bad to be this excited over it? I can only liken it to getting your first fave on DA.

OH GOD GUYS, DARK OF THE MOON. SPOILERS/REACTIONS UNDER THE CUT. Soundwave. Oh my god, Soundwave. Him and Laserbeak were such total badasses and I am going to squee so hard and repeat Bolts here: SO FUCKING HOT. Oh my god. BUT Y U DIE, SOUNDWAVE? Y U DO DIS TO ME? QAQ *hugs WFC Soundwave* I would've cried so hard at the deaths of Ironhide and Soundwave if it wasn't for the fact Sean was with me and I wasn't currently "What the FUCK." raging over the lack of reaction/emotion from anyone over 'Hide's death and total nonchalance at their planet being fucking destroyed. OH HAI CYBERTRON, DON'T GIVE A FUCK WHAT HAPPENS TO YOU! Lalalala! :D" Speaking of - anyone else get that reference/nod to Cosmic Rust with his death? FFFF. AND MEGATRON YOU NARCISSISTIC BASTARD. Lookit you gloatin' on your stone Lincoln chair. LOL Y U IMMITATIN' YO' G1 SELF? Also in response to a few people raging over Carly's speech to Megatron at the near end - It's actually plausible. I mean, I'm sure Sam's told her oodles about the decepticons and Megatron and what not, and given his personality it's not that hard to play off of and feed that over-confident, proud, dominating personality of his. It doesn't really take a genius to know how to manipulate that. WHERE THE FUCK WAS SILVERBOLT. WHAT THE FUCK WAS WITH QUE. CHANGE THE HEAD AND I SWEAR, YOU HAD WHEELJACK. Y U FUCK WITH US, BAY? WHY DIDN'T YOU JUST KEEP DINO AS MIRAGE? >:( .....WHY THE FUCK DID ROADBUSTER AND LEADFOOT SPEAK BUT TOPSPIN DIDN'T? You obviously can give two out of three wreckers a personality, but not the third? All in all I really enjoyed the film. I will probably pirate it until it comes out on DVD to watch over and over and try to catch things i missed. OH AND ALSO. It's not TOO 3D-ish or whatever, but you can seriously tell it was shot using the camera. It really does create depth and a sense of immersion into the surroundings and each scene, that I really liked. It wasn't overwhelming, other than a few animation things that had me going, "Dear god, my seat doesn't recline far enough for me to see it properly!" and cursing the lack of glasses-friendly Real3D glasses out there for these kinds of movies.

I don't know about any of you, but I adore movie scores. I finally managed to find a torrent/rar file download of the Dark of the Moon score. Going to see the movie in a few hours, whoo! Gettin' super excited. :3 The file's here, if anyone's interested in downloadin' it! And I don't know about anyone else, but as I listen to it again, it's got a bit of Hanz Zimmer influence to it. A few songs (Sentinel Prime, for one) remind me of the Last Samurai score.
Oh, she knew alright. Bitches only dream of gettin' that. I have such a dirty, dirty mind.

Hey Guys. GUYS. Guys. Hey. Hey guys. I gots a tumblr. I'm slowly updating my TF Makeup looks, and it'll primarily be for said makeup looks. :> Going to be doing a G1 Scorponok look monday, check it out! One of the pharmacy techs at the hospital I work at requested it. XD SO AWESOME, GUYS. Can't wait. You all can request looks, too! Just drop a comment on me and I'll see what I can do!

I started doing flower inspired looks, since I don't have the right colors to do a few of the Transformers I want to do. SO. FLOWERS. Yesterday's look was inspired by my two gorgeous Bleeding Heart bushes. Shiro Cosmetics in Like-Like, Clefairy, Vileplume and Team Rocket Today's look was inspired by the ever beautiful Stargazer Lily. Shiro Cosmetics in iShadow White, Porygon, Team Rocket, Rupee

This time it isn't a Transformers look. :> I got the idea to do an inverted eye look. Instead of the dark colors on the outside/crease, why not use the light colors? Shiro Cosmetics iShadow trio in White, Aluminum, and Black. It came out looking more like an Orca Whale than inverted, but I like it. :D

Despite the horrible, horrible bug-slash-food poisoning I have, I did a makeup look today. ALSO Totally pimping Shiro Cosmetic's little picture contest! Giveaway rules here! She's looking for Eye of the Day looks using ONLY shiro cosmetics eyeshadows (primers, mascara, eyeliners can be from someone else since she doesn't sell those) to celebrate the new PORTAL themed eyeshadow collection (go to Her Shop Page to check it out! :D FOR SCIENCE.) Every picture she chooses gets a $5 store credit towards their next purchase! SO ONTO MY LOOK. JAZZ (lol I'm sensing a pattern here - Soundwave, Rumble, Frenzy, and now Jazz...) SHIRO COSMETICS in iShadow White, Dimitri, Gyarados, and iShadow Black. Styli-Style mascara in Electric Blue, Prestige eyeliner in Rhapsody.

WHELP, I might just be doing tutorials on how to get these looks, MAYBE, though my camera on my phone is horrible and my actual camera is...horrible. Anyways. FRENZY DAY TODAY 8D I had fun with this one. I might, when I have a day off, do one eye Frenzy and the other eye Rumble. Shiro Cosmetics in Subrosia, iShadow Black, and Dunsparce (in the corner/half of lower lid); iShadow Aluminum for highlight. Any requests? :3

So I've been slacking on my makeup look-of-the-day's. I finally got my iShadow collection from Shiro Cosmetics, so I've been playing around with it. Did a smoky eye sunday, another look that was actually apart of the thumbnails for the collection, and then these three. The first one didn't have anything to do with the iShadow collection. :I This one was inspired after LadyDragon82's latest installment of Crackalackalicious. Soundwave and the gang finally showed up, and I adored Frenzy/Rumble times that I did a Rumble inspired look. I went by the G1 cartoon, so in my mind, RIBFIR. Shiro Cosmetics in Majora's Mask and Ocarina. Skyfire look. Shiro Cosmetics iShadow White, iShadow Black, Subrosia. This one's my favorite, and I'm wearing it today! Wheeljack look with iShadow White, Dimitri, and Link!

Lookin' for some new music for my playlist. Lately I've been into trance/clubbing techno, but I don't really have any on my computer, so I've been listening to Fat Boy Slim, Gorillaz, Daft Punk, Paul Oakenfold, and club remixes of Gaga, Kylie Minogue, etc. 

Anyone got any suggestions for me?

OH MY GOD GUYS THE NEW EPISODE OF TF:PRIME. TF:PRIME, OH MY GOD. 

I WAS ALL HOLY SHIT THROUGH THE WHOLE THING. AND THEN THE TEASER FOR NEXT WEEK? I WANT NOW. OH MY GOD.

I'm gonna go watch it again.

This was Tuesday's look (I did a Star Wars theme for the 4th, but didn't get a good picture). MEGATRON inspired look with Magneton, Subrosia and Hyperbeam! :) I love playing with all these colors, lol.

Well yesterday, after re-watching the DOTM trailer and seeing Shockwave in his tentacle-monster riding glory, I wanted to do a Shockwave inspired eyeshadow look. Shiro Cosmetics in Temple of Time (with Magneton layered over), Team Rocket, and Lance the Dragon Trainer, with Styli-Style mascara in purple and Prestige eyeliner in Masqerade. On my lips I put Jigglypuff, but I didn't take a pic of that.

I've noticed on my friends list it's customary to do at least one HOTROD trolling. So here's mine. Also, icon is totally relevant. I could see Roddy pumping his ego up like that every morning. I couldn't help myself! I was listening to that "Autobot Love Song" while doing my makeup, and since I'd already done a Devastator look, I decided to go with Hot Rod/Rodimus Prime. colors used were SHIRO COSMETICS in Charmander, Pikachu (mixed inner corner); Hearts (outer corner/crease); Concrete Minerals in Napalm (middle lid blended into inner and outer corners; under eye) which is a really awesome bright ass orange with a gold undertone; and Shiro Cosmetics Subrosia for a liner. You guys should check these cosmetic stores out :D Concrete Minerals gives you a ten-gram jar full of product for like..5.99 for full size, and their samples are the five-gram jars which is huge for..I don't know how much. But it's awesome. And Shiro? Geekiness and really smooth, easily blendable colors that you don't need a primer or a base for. Love love love these two companies. Shiro Cosmetics Concrete Minerals

So I didn't get a picture of my easter makeup, but that's okay. :D I used my new Concrete Minerals makeup that I had gotten for that look. And after being told i looked like a drag queen by my boyfriend on Easter, I kinda sat back and didn't really do many make-up looks this week. I did, however, end up with an unintentional War For Cybertron Soundwave look: (Colors used: SHIRO COSMETICS Magneton (silver-ish with a purple base and blue flecks), Poliwrath (smokey blue with silver flecks), and Zora (teal blue); Styli Style color lash mascara in blue, navy blue eyeliner) The picture doesn't do it justice. It looked a-frickin-mazing. and then yesterday's look, since I'd already done the other two, was a G1 Starscream look: (SHIRO COSMETICS Like-like, Subrosia, and Zora (liner and lower lid) ) All in all, I had fun doing these. :> Anyone else have any requests?

Went with a Skywarp look today! VOP! SHIRO COSMETICS in Like-Like (with Temple of Time layered over), Spiritomb, Zubat, and Hyperbeam; Merle Norman eyeliner pencil in ebony, Styli-style colorlash mascara in Purple. Probably should've done something green for Earth Day, but the purples just begged to be used!

suggested a Drag Strip look today, so here we go! SHIRO Cosmetics in PIKACHU, CHARMANDER, HEARTS, SUBROSIA, RATTATA, WOBBUFFET; Merle Norman eyeliner in ebony, Styli-Style colorlash mascara in Blue. This was fun! :D Came out great! Pikachu: Bright yellow-gold with red sparkle. Charmander: Pretty tangerine orange with gold flecks. Hearts: Bright, true red Rattata: Bright, vibrant crayola purple Subrosia: Darker, almost blood-red; maybe brick red. Wobbuffet: pretty pastel blue with blue pearl sheen.

I am into blues this week. :I Yesterday I did a Blurr inspired eyeshadow: (Shiro cosmetics in Manectric, Squirtle, and Gyrados; Maybelline define-a-line eyeliner in Teal waters, and Styli-Style colorlash mascara in blue) and today is Thundercracker. (Shiro Cosmetics in Likelike (with temple of time layered over for that creamy-silver look), Squirtle, and Midna; same eyeliner and mascara.) I'm having way too much fun with all these colors. :> Someone give me another bot/con to do next! OH, and a link to Shiro Cosmetics!

Another Tranformers inspired look today! :> Can you guess which cons i based this off of? SHIRO COSMETICS in Lance the Dragon Trainer (gray-purple with gold sparkle), Rattata (bright d-con purple), Hyperbeam (black) and Loreal HIP duo Eyeshadow in Mischief (Gold side only!) for liner :)

While trying to think up of different ways to use all seventy of my SHIRO COSMETICS eyeshadows, I came up with a DEVASTATOR look today. ACID (bright yellow/green) on the majority of my lid. SPIRITOMB (d-conish purple with green sparkle) on the outer corner and into the crease. GENGAR (black-purple) to lightly shade into SPIRITOMB on the outer corner. HEARTS (bright, true red) in the very inner corner of my eye - not too much. HYPERBEAM (black with rainbow sparkle) lower lid and liner on the upper lid. Next time, I might just leave HEARTS out all together and use WEEPINBELL (much more yellow-green chartreuse), but I wanted that flash of red for a throwback to the optics. :)
This is what I wake up to, today. XD Sean's now playing with and posing my toys. Stud!Alert just seems to be missing the little bowtie, but he'd make a great Chip'n'dales dancer.

ajfhjkdfg. Why is it every time I'm bored, I somehow wander into my bathroom, open my makeup kit up, and mess around with all of my eyeshadows? :I 

..I swear to god, I'm going to end up looking like Rainbow Bright when SHIROCOSMETIC's "Legends" collection arrives. Zelda inspired vegan eyeshadows are going to be my downfall. If I ever get more money, I'll probably end up getting her "Super Effective!" Pokemon-themed collection too.

And is it sad to admit I want to learn how to make my own eyeshadows, just so I can make "Transformers" inspired colors/sets? "Devastator Set" would consist of Constructicon Green, Decepticon Purple and Cybertron gunmetal gray. "Dinobots Set" would be Autobot Red, Sunstreaker Yellow/gold, and Silverbolt gray/silver. :I I'm already planning colors without materials or money. what the hell.
Diva!Alert does not approve of this placement. Or lack of friendlies.

WHY. WHY MUST TF:P BRING IN AWESOME CHARACTERS ONLY FOR ONE EPISODE? >:I

GOD DAMNIT, WHEELJACK.

WHY THE FUCK'S HE GOTTA LEAVE.

<sub>He had a sexy, sexy voice, too QAQ</sub>

On a totally unrelated note, went grocery shopping with my niece, and when we walked into the toy aisle, she pointed out Red Alert for me. :D He's now standing on my desk amidst baddies from TF, Star Wars and JTHM/I Feel Sick. and a fossil. With his hip cocked out. it's quite funny. Diva!Alert is not amused.

Will post a picture once my phone's charged.

So I'm sittin' here, morning after a blizzard, eating cherry pie for breakfast and reliving my childhood saturday mornings (Shut up, i know it's monday. I can pretend, lol) by watching Freakazoid cartoons, when the Lobe makes his appearance. "Hark," I exclaim, "That voice! I know that voice! That throaty, english accent, it calls to me!" So torn between the actor who plays Shockwave and the actor who plays Sark, I hit up good ol' IMDB. It's Sark. David Fuckin' Warner. hell yeah. I scrolled through the rest of the cast, and I must admit; I'm shocked. A lot of these characters are played by well known actors. Frank Welker, for one. :D David Kaufman, Ricardo Montalban (Classic movie actor, for those who don't know, such as Naked Gun)..Spielberg did a great job with this cartoon. :D I wish it would've had more seasons/episodes.

If you really don't know me by now, I'll post. OR Ngh. The new Pontiac Firebird/Firebreather (it uses a camaro body; tradition, man) is so fucking sexy. But ever since the Viper came out in 95-96(ish), I've wanted one. Especially an ACR. OH GOD. NO. WAIT. I forgot the Falcon QAQ ...Oh god, I'm so indecisive.
Just dumped a whole bunch of art into my scrapbook, lol. Old art is old, full of wildlife and original characters and crap. Check it out if you want :>

I would like all my LJ friends to comment about how you got to know me. But I want you to LIE. That's right. Just make it up. Then if you like, after you comment, copy this to your journal so I can do the same.

If you could make soundtracks for your favorite characters, or fanfics, what songs would be on there? What type of themes would you go for? What about certain songs would strike cords to you when it came to certain characters? 

I've noticed, while listening to my playlist (i literally just put my whole music folder into winamp and hit random), that dark or suspenseful instrumentals strike a chord with how I've read, and seen, Megatron portrayed. Old 80's/early 90's rap (Such as Beastie Boys) always reminds me of Rumble/Frenzy. Mindless Self Indulgence songs remind me of Zim, for some reason. 

If you could pick a song off of your head-cannon playlist for any character or fanfic, what would it be?

Is it just me or does this new TESLA car (from the 2011 North American International Auto Show in Detroit) look like an uber weeaboo, kabuki-fied DRIFT? I can't unsee it now I've suggested it. EDIT: FRONT VIEW MAKES THIS MORE OBVIOUS :U

was the BEST EVER.

Friday night was the Green 17 Tour concert. Twopointeight, a band from Sweden, were the openers and they did an awesome job. Definitely going to have to find a site where I can get a cd or download music from. Then there was Street Dogs, who the lead singer was the singer from Dropkick Murphy's. And then of course, FLOGGING MOLLY. Omg. The balconies were shaking so bad from everyone bouncing and dancing along, I thought we were gonna get smooshed. 

All in all, I had so much fun. <3

And now, I'm sitting here at the computer watching Zoolander while dealing with a rather horrid migrane. Thank you, Twilight Princess. Damn you and your freakin' hot spring water barrel run.

That Sweet Sixteen show on MTV? Yeah. 

Someone needs to fucking beat the shit out of those kids and tell them no. They should be GRATEFUL someone has acknowleged them on their sixteenth. I didn't even HAVE a party. I didn't get gifts. I got a "Hey, yeah. happy birthday." . No 300K car, no cake, nothing. we couldn't afford it, because earlier that year my stepfather died. And you know what? That was okay. I understood. I was happy that my mom and sister remembered. So fuck you rich, snobby, vain little bitches. I hope your families get robbed or go bankrupt.

Buttons was a baby dutch lops bunny I had gotten for my sister for Christmas. Sometime during 3AM and 7AM, he passed away.

He was adorable, for the short week we had had him. All of us had gotten attached, and would laugh at how his ears flopped all around when he chased the cats around the living room, or how he'd look like Gizmo (the gremlin) when he stood on his hind legs.

My sister's devastated. It wasn't her fault, either, he had just gotten sick yesterday and we all didn't try to force enough water into him. My sister tried so hard though, giving him two baths yesterday to clean him up and changing his cage bedding several times; forcing water into him for a while..and he had seemed to be getting better.

I'm so sorry.

Okay, so I know this game is like, uber rare, but I really want to get it for Sean. 

http://cgi.ebay.com/ws/eBayISAPI.dll?ViewItem&ih=002&sspagename=STRK%3AMEBI%3AIT&viewitem=&item=120064596773&rd=1&rd=1

Right now I'm winning, but that stupid gamermom person is probably one of those last minute, put in a real high bid with two seconds left in the auction person, and I hope to god that doesn't happen. Every other person selling it on Ebay accepts paypal only. This is the only one that is accepting anything else. I can't pay with paypal, cause they take too long to transfer money, and if I won the auction they'd put it right back up for sale if I didn't come up with it in two days. 

SIGH, I hate ebay.

After extensive research due to the untimely death to the Legendary Croc hunter, I've found it wasn't a sting that killed him, but that the ray's stinger had pierced through his heart. Supposidly it had entered the body under the ribs and made it to the pumping organ. 

The 44 year old had left behind a Wife, Terri, an eight year old daughter Bindi Sue, and a three year old son Bob, as well as adoring fans world wide. He died doing what he loved, and I'm sure he wouldn't have had it any other way. 

Conservation has lost a very dear friend, and I hope that, even though he's gone, that message he tried to express about respecting nature and it's less loved, scale-y members (who I personally adore..I love reptiles). 

Rest in Peace, Steve Irwin.

Well, I guess I'll start from last thursday. I walked up to M-59 and Mound to the new petstore that just opened up, and applied for a job. While I was there, I saw the most gorgeous kingsnake baby, and I have made it my sole mission, should I be able to afford it (after getting a liscense and my GED and getting into college and such) that I will have that snake. I got to hold it and just..aww. I was in love. 

Out of all the snakes they had there, I wanted that one. 

Well, my sister comes home today with a baby albino cornsnake, ((illegally bought, I might add-she had to be 18 to get it, and the guy who sold it to her got fired because he didn't card her or Mike)) and I love it, but everytime I go to touch it, I panic and end up pulling away. I don't know why I do this, I just do..I never did that with the king snake. That beauty even bit me, and I loved it even more. But the cornsnake...something about it just scares me, and I am /NOT/ afraid of snakes. 

I wish I knew what was wrong. >>; Ah well. It'll be gone tomorrow. My mom is making them return it ASAP, because she's terrified of anything that isn't a cat or dog or fish.

Sometimes I really hate being a female. ~.~ Damn period. 

I feel like i'm going to throw up. x__X
